    "notes": "",
    "docHtml": "<p>A flanged or spiked iron head lashed to a wooden haft with leather and iron bindings, this is the common mace of footmen, fyrdsmen, and city guards. Lighter than its steel-handled cousin and easier to maintain, it nonetheless delivers bone-cracking force to crush shields and helm. The wood shaft flexes slightly on impact, distributing shock upward through the wielder's arms.</p>\n",
